Bank of Nova Scotia Awards Chief Executive Waugh $10.9 Million for 2010

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-02-28T13:33:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/bank-of-nova-scotia-awards-chief-executive-waugh-10-9-million-for-2010.html
  Bank of Nova Scotia  increased Chief
Executive Officer Richard Waugh’s compensation by 10 percent in
2010 after  Canada ’s third-largest bank posted record profit.  Waugh was awarded C$10.7 million ($10.9 million) in direct
compensation for the year that ended Oct. 31, compared with
C$9.7 million for the previous year, the Toronto-based bank said
today in a regulatory filing. The figures don’t include pension
costs.  Scotiabank also increased Waugh’s annual salary beginning
in June to C$1.5 million from C$1 million, the first time since
2003 his base had been increased, the bank said.  Scotiabank is the fourth Canadian lender to disclose
executive compensation. Royal Bank of Canada awarded CEO Gordon Nixon C$11 million, while Toronto-Dominion Bank awarded CEO
Edmund Clark C$11.3 million.  Bank of Montreal’s pay for CEO William Downe was C$9.54
million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
